        {
            "id": "0030",
            "text": "This is the place that exhibited the old form of justice. Before the Sundering, the Ancient Eulex disputed mortal charges and sin. One would enter a trial by combat, allowing the favor of their Ancient to serve as arbiter, against the accuser. This could even be invoked for petty charges.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "text": "Goodness.",
                    "next": "0035",
                    "npcIds": [
                        11
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "text": "How does this reconcile with Daethos proclaiming providence?",
                    "next": "0031",
                    "npcIds": [
                        11
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "text": "How come this isn't in practice anymore?",
                    "next": "0032",
                    "npcIds": [
                        11
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "text": "Not to cut this short, but could I trouble you for your wares?",
                    "next": "0020",
                    "npcIds": [
                        11
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "text": "I'm intrigued. How does this work, exactly?",
                    "next": "0033",
                    "npcIds": [
                        11
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "text": "Oh my. Show me the roster.",
                    "next": "0034",
                    "npcIds": [
                        11
                    ],
                    "action": "setRoster"
                }
            ],
            "npcIds": [
                11
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "0031",
            "text": "It does seem that it would be cross, and it brings up the worship adhering to the Ancients as opposed to Daethos. However, trial by combat was seen as a legitimate form of exculpation due to many of the trials taking place between worshippers of different ancients, and one could proclaim Daethos as exceptional and before all being. The Eulex meant to poise your belief against your adversary's, and retains this honor with the advent of Daethos.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "text": "What is the Ancient Eulex, again?",
                    "next": "0030",
                    "npcIds": [
                        11
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "text": "If this is true, how come it is no longer in practice?",
                    "next": "0032",
                    "npcIds": [
                        11
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "text": "Wonderful. Show me the roster.",
                    "next": "0034",
                    "npcIds": [
                        11
                    ],
                    "action": "setRoster"
                }
            ],
            "npcIds": [
                11
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "0032",
            "text": "With the proliferation of Daethos, the practice of trial by combat had waned since its use to show favor of a single Ancient was seen as a perversion to the blessing of Daethos and our providence. Not to mention the Ancients role in the Sundering, with some regions--even within majority adherent provinces, seeing it as heretical.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "text": "What is the Ancient Eulex, again?",
                    "next": "0030",
                    "npcIds": [
                        11
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "text": "Would this not be accepted by the Seyr, or followers of Daethos?",
                    "next": "0031",
                    "npcIds": [
                        11
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "text": "I love what I'm hearing. Show me the roster.",
                    "next": "0034",
